 Spotify 宣布盈利并增加了数百万订阅者，但还削减了不太受欢迎的曲目的版税https://www.nme.com/news/music/spotify-announce-profit-and-millions-more-subscribers-but-also-royalty-cuts-to-less-popular-tracks-3521362?utm_source=rss&utm_medium= rss&utm_campaign=spotify 宣布利润和数百万订阅者，但版税也削减到不太受欢迎的曲目Emma WilkesWed, 25 Oct 2023 17:55:52 +0000 Music NewsNewsSpotify https://www.nme.com/?p=3521362 <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/spotify-mateusz-slodkowski-1.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="Spotify 徽标" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/spotify-mateusz-slodkowski-1.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/spotify-mateusz-slodkowski-1-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/spotify-mateusz-slodkowski-1-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/spotify-mateusz-slodkowski-1-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/spotify-mateusz-slodkowski-1-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/spotify-mateusz-slodkowski-1-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p>据报道，这些有争议的变化将为主要唱片公司带来最大的利益</p><p><a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/spotify-announce-profit-and-millions-more-subscribers-but-also-royalty-cuts-to-less-popular-tracks-3521362">Spotify 宣布盈利并增加了数百万订阅者，但同时也削减了不太受欢迎的曲目的版税，这一消息</a>首先出现在<a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a>上。</p> ; <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/spotify-mateusz-slodkowski-1.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="Spotify 徽标" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/spotify-mateusz-slodkowski-1.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/spotify-mateusz-slodkowski-1-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/spotify-mateusz-slodkowski-1-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/spotify-mateusz-slodkowski-1-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/spotify-mateusz-slodkowski-1-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/spotify-mateusz-slodkowski-1-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> <a href="https://www.nme.com/tag/spotify">Spotify</a>宣布，尽管该公司第三季度利润和用户增长好于预期，但不太受欢迎的曲目将不会获得任何版税。</p><p> 6 月至 9 月，这家瑞典流媒体服务的付费用户增加了 600 万，使其总数达到 2.26 亿。这超出了其付费用户数量将突破 2.24 亿大关的预测。</p><p>尽管取得了这些收益，但<a href="https://www.billboard.com/pro/spotify-changing-how-pays-artists-stream-thresholds/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Billboard</em>报道称</a>Spotify 正在重组其版税系统，并计划将之前获得 Spotify 0.5% 版税池的曲目货币化。”据报道，该计划将于明年初实施。</p><p>版税制度的变化将使更多成熟的艺术家和唱片公司受益，而与旧制度的最大区别在于，一首曲目在开始产生版税之前需要达到最低的年度流媒体数量。</p><p>据报道，Spotify 还计划打击“欺诈”，并将对其认为有罪的发行商和唱片公司处以经济处罚。白噪声或环境声音等非音乐曲目也必须达到“最短播放时间长度”才能产生版税。 </p><figure id="attachment_3511134" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3511134" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="size-full wp-image-3511134" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/The-Spotify-logo.jpg" alt="Spotify" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/The-Spotify-logo.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/The-Spotify-logo-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/The-Spotify-logo-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/The-Spotify-logo-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/The-Spotify-logo-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/The-Spotify-logo-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3511134" class="wp-caption-text"> Spotify – 图片来源：Getty</figcaption></figure><p> <em>Billboard</em>声称，最近与 Spotify 进行谈判的主要唱片公司可能会同意这些变化，因为他们将因此赚更多的钱。</p><p>据报道，在 7 月份的财报电话会议上，环球音乐集团首席执行官卢西恩·格兰奇 (Lucian Grange) 宣布与 Spotify 达成一项“新扩大的协议”，声称该协议将“以艺术家为中心”，并将惠及“拥有真正粉丝群的真正艺术家”。</p><p>与此同时，本月早些时候有传言称， <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/spotify-reportedly-launching-new-supremium-tier-with-more-features-3511133">该流媒体服务正准备推出新的“Supremium”级别</a>，其中包含额外的功能，但价格更高。</p><p> <em><a href="https://www.independent.co.uk/tech/spotify-premium-extra-hifi-free-latest-b2425510.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">《独立报》</a></em>的一篇报道称，新版本的价格将是当前价格的两倍，为 19.99 美元（16.33 英镑），并且将提供无损音频——目前 Apple Music 免费提供这一功能。</p><p>据报道，该层还将包括有关听力的新统计数据、 <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/spotify-to-offer-15-free-hours-of-audiobook-streaming-per-month-3509117">新的有声读物功能</a>以及人工智能播放列表生成工具。 <em>《独立报》</em>表示，技术专家 Chris Messina 已经注意到了这些变化，据该出版物称，他“发现 Spotify 提到了这一更新”。</p><p>上个月，该平台<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/spotify-launches-tool-for-artists-to-pay-to-feature-on-home-screen-3500424">推出了 Showcase——一种新工具，允许艺术家付费在网站主页上推广他们的音乐</a>。 </p><div class="td-a-ad id_inline_ad1 id_ad_content-horiz-center"><div class="apester-media" data-manual-top-desktop="64" data-manual-top-mobile="55" data-token="5644b81019aec6d348309b65" data-context="true" data-tags="" data-fallback="true"></div></div><p> <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/spotify-announce-profit-and-millions-more-subscribers-but-also-royalty-cuts-to-less-popular-tracks-3521362">Spotify 宣布盈利并增加了数百万订阅者，但同时也削减了不太受欢迎的曲目的版税，这一消息</a>首先出现在<a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a>上。</p> ;
